MSFT
OAI
MSFT and OAI maintain a long-term strategic partnership which was originally established in 2019. In
the agreement MSFT is a major investor in OAI and the companies have reciprocal revenue-sharing
arrangements. MSFT accounts for OAI’s revenue through equity method accounting, which implications
we have outlined previously. Further in this agreement MSFT hold rights to OAI’s intellectual property,
including models and infrastructure, for integration into our products. However, as of September 2025
MSFT and OAI have signed a non-binding memorandum of understanding for the next phase of their
partnership. They are working to finalize contractual terms in a definitive agreement.
NVDA
CRWV
In April 2023, NVDA owned a beneficial owner of more than 5% of CWRV outstanding capital stock. As
of June 2025 NVDA owned ~7% of CRWV’s outstanding shares or ~ 24,278mn representing a market
value of $2.883bn.
NVDA
OAI
In October 2024 NVDA invested $0.1bn as part of OAI’s $6.6bn round. Then on September 22, 2025, it
was announced that NVDA intends to progressively invest up to $100bn in OAI as part of a new
partnership where OAI will build and deploy at least 10 gigawatts of AI data centers.
OAI
CRWV
As part of the $11.9 bn strategic deal announced on March 10, 2025, OAI will become an investor in
CRWV through the issuance of $0.35bn of CRWV stock.
OAI
AMD
As part of a strategic deal announced on October 6, 2025. AMD has issued OAI a warrant for up to .16
bn shares at a par value $0.01 per share of AMD common stock valued at ~$34bn based on an October
6, 2025 stock price of $212 or ~10% of AMD market cap. The warrants are structured to vest as specific
milestones are achieved.
